						               													<description>Brothers at War is wargame system to land battles in the American Civil War (ACW) on 6mm to 20mm scale. &amp;#10;The basic fighting unit is a company or a battery of artilley. These are grouped into divisions. &amp;#10;Turns are performed by alternate activation of divisions, with the quality of the commanders determining some issues.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Basic unit types are: infantry, cavalry, artillery and special units (General, Officer, Banner, Skirmisher). &amp;#10;Points system for units and army lists for points based games. &amp;#10;The army lists can be used to convert historical orders of battle, into lists for games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The objective is to provide an easy, agile and adaptable rules system for the simulation of combat in the American Civil War. &amp;#10;The definitions of range of weapons were based on historical sources and serious publications, in particular the book &amp;ldquo;Small Arms at Gettysburg&amp;rdquo;, by Joseph G. Bilby. &amp;#10;Likewise, the rules for combat formations and for the historical characteristics of each army were also the target of research in specialized bibliography on the subject.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
